2. VoIP, or Voice over Internet Protocol, is a communication technology that enables you to make phone calls to be made through a broadband internet connection rather than regular analog telephone lines. Voice over Long Term Evolution (VoLTE) is a digital packet voice service provided over IP via an LTE access network, utilizing IMS technology.

3. Berry (1980) defined acculturation as ‘Changes induced into cultural systems as a result of diffusion of cultural elements in both directions’. He further ascertained that four modes of acculturation, namely integration, assimilation, separation and deculturation (Berry, 1980; [Nahavandi & Malekzadeh, 1988](https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/10.1177/02560909241236548#bibr9-02560909241236548)), determine how the acquirer and acquired firms adapt to each other to avoid any conflict.

