Biographies
-----------

**Chhavi Mehta** is an Associate Professor in the Finance and Accounting area at the International Management Institute (IMI), New Delhi. She has nearly 29 years of diverse experience in teaching, research, training and consultancy. She teaches financial reporting and analysis, cost and management accounting, financial management and business valuation. She has published various research papers in reputed national and international journals. She regularly conducts management development programmes (MDPs), which are very well received by industry professionals. She has also worked on a government-funded research project granted by the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority of India (IRDAI).

e-mail: [chhavi.mehta@imi.edu](mailto:chhavi.mehta@imi.edu)

**Monika Chopra** is currently an Associate Professor and Finance Area Chair at the International Management Institute, New Delhi. She has 21 years of teaching experience. Her areas of teaching and research are security analysis and portfolio management, business valuation, private equity and corporate finance. She has authored several research papers in top-rated national and international journals and has also coauthored two books. She has conducted several MDPs on finance for non-finance executives. In CFA Society India, she is looking after the investment research challenge, ethics challenge and Women in Finance Initiative.

e-mail: [monika.chopra@imi.edu](mailto:monika.chopra@imi.edu)

**Sanjay Dhamija** is currently a Professor in the finance and accounting area at the International Management Institute, New Delhi. He has over 38 years of experience in industry and academia. He has authored 12 books and published several research papers and case studies in national and international journals and case repositories in finance, accounting, law and corporate governance. He was conferred the ‘Best Teacher’ award by MDI, Gurgaon and the ‘Best Trainer’ award by IMI, New Delhi. His case was awarded as the ‘Best Case’ in Finance, Economics, Business and Political Environment at the 40th Anniversary Case Conference at IIM Bangalore.

e-mail: [sdhamija@imi.edu](mailto:sdhamija@imi.edu)

